#. <section class="sutta" id="sn45.1"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn45.1:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 45"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 45"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn45.1:0.2"
msgid "1. Avijjāvagga"
msgstr "1. Ignorance"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn45.1:0.3"
msgid "1. Avijjāsutta"
msgstr "1. Ignorance"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi5.1"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn45.1:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​"
msgstr "So I have heard."

msgctxt "sn45.1:1.2"
msgid ""
"ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, "
"Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery."

msgctxt "sn45.1:1.3"
msgid "Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr "There the Buddha addressed the mendicants:"

msgctxt "sn45.1:1.4"
msgid "“bhikkhavo”ti."
msgstr "“Mendicants!”"

msgctxt "sn45.1:1.5"
msgid "“Bhadante”ti te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ."
msgstr "“Venerable sir,” they replied."

msgctxt "sn45.1:1.6"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr "The Buddha said this:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
#. VAR: anvadeva → anudeva (si, pts1, mr)
msgctxt "sn45.1:2.1"
msgid ""
"“Avijjā, bhikkhave, pubbaṅgamā akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ samāpattiyā, anvadeva "
"ahirikaṃ anottappaṃ."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, ignorance precedes the attainment of unskillful qualities, with "
"lack of conscience and prudence following along."

msgctxt "sn45.1:2.2"
msgid "Avijjāgatassa, bhikkhave, aviddasuno micchādiṭṭhi pahoti;"
msgstr "An ignoramus, sunk in ignorance, gives rise to wrong view."

msgctxt "sn45.1:2.3"
msgid "micchādiṭṭhissa micchāsaṅkappo pahoti;"
msgstr "Wrong view gives rise to wrong thought."

msgctxt "sn45.1:2.4"
msgid "micchāsaṅkappassa micchāvācā pahoti;"
msgstr "Wrong thought gives rise to wrong speech."

msgctxt "sn45.1:2.5"
msgid "micchāvācassa micchākammanto pahoti;"
msgstr "Wrong speech gives rise to wrong action."

msgctxt "sn45.1:2.6"
msgid "micchākammantassa micchāājīvo pahoti;"
msgstr "Wrong action gives rise to wrong livelihood."

msgctxt "sn45.1:2.7"
msgid "micchāājīvassa micchāvāyāmo pahoti;"
msgstr "Wrong livelihood gives rise to wrong effort."

msgctxt "sn45.1:2.8"
msgid "micchāvāyāmassa micchāsati pahoti;"
msgstr "Wrong effort gives rise to wrong mindfulness."

msgctxt "sn45.1:2.9"
msgid "micchāsatissa micchāsamādhi pahoti."
msgstr "Wrong mindfulness gives rise to wrong immersion."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi5.2"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn45.1:3.1"
msgid ""
"Vijjā ca kho, bhikkhave, pubbaṅgamā kusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ samāpattiyā, "
"anvadeva hirottappaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Knowledge precedes the attainment of skillful qualities, with conscience and "
"prudence following along."

msgctxt "sn45.1:3.2"
msgid "Vijjāgatassa, bhikkhave, viddasuno sammādiṭṭhi pahoti;"
msgstr "A sage, firm in knowledge, gives rise to right view."

msgctxt "sn45.1:3.3"
msgid "sammādiṭṭhissa sammāsaṅkappo pahoti;"
msgstr "Right view gives rise to right thought."

msgctxt "sn45.1:3.4"
msgid "sammāsaṅkappassa sammāvācā pahoti;"
msgstr "Right thought gives rise to right speech."

msgctxt "sn45.1:3.5"
msgid "sammāvācassa sammākammanto pahoti;"
msgstr "Right speech gives rise to right action."

msgctxt "sn45.1:3.6"
msgid "sammākammantassa sammāājīvo pahoti;"
msgstr "Right action gives rise to right livelihood."

msgctxt "sn45.1:3.7"
msgid "sammāājīvassa sammāvāyāmo pahoti;"
msgstr "Right livelihood gives rise to right effort."

msgctxt "sn45.1:3.8"
msgid "sammāvāyāmassa sammāsati pahoti;"
msgstr "Right effort gives rise to right mindfulness."

msgctxt "sn45.1:3.9"
msgid "sammāsatissa sammāsamādhi pahotī”ti."
msgstr "Right mindfulness gives rise to right immersion.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn45.1:3.10"
msgid "Paṭhamaṃ."
msgstr ""
